n heroes and heroines and features detailed illustrations on various phenomena of the heroic, its figures, functions, mediality and practice. Methodologically, the Compendium heroicum applies a broad historical approach – ranging from the ancient world to the present day – as well as a cross-cultural perspective, focusing on the importance of heroic figures within and beyond European contexts. Researchers at the <a rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" href=\"https://www.sfb948.uni-freiburg.de/\" target=\"_blank\">Collaborative Research Center 948</a> as well as external contributors author collaboratively written articles to be published on the \"Compendium heroicum\". All articles will be digitally accessible worldwide free of charge (Open Access).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>English edition available</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since late 2022, the <em>Compendium heroicum</em> is available in English. In its English edition, the <em>Compendium heroicum</em> publishes translations of its existing German articles as well as original articles in English. By summer 2024, both editions are expected to reach a similar scope in terms of content. The purpose of the multilingual edition is to facilitate access to the research finding of the Collaborative Research Center for international readers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"oes-external-link\"} -->\n<p class=\"oes-external-link\"><a href=\"https://www.compendium-heroicum.de/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Compendium Heroicum - Das Online-Lexikon des Sonderforschungsbereichs 948 „Helden – Heroisierungen – Heroismen“</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->','UC: Compendium heroicum (Version 1.1)','','publish','closed','closed','','uc-compendium-heroicum-version-1-1','','','2023-02-03 18:42:07','2023-02-03 18:42:07','',0,'http://demo.open-encyclopedia-system.org/?post_type=demo_article&#038;p=1626',0,'demo_article','',0),(1627,2,'202